cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the operating principles of deep neural networks (DNNs) and proposes an algorithm to provide better insights into their decision-making processes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) as DNNs are widely used in these fields. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the functioning of neural networks. Finally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a potential sub-category as the paper mentions the vulnerability of DNNs to adversarial attacks.
